Time. You will need to gain years of experience in the craft of making stringed instruments. If you are fortunate, you can find an apprenticeship with an already established Luthier (or two, or three.) However, actually going out there and building them even n your own is a good way to start. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9c/Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet1.jpeg/460px-Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet1.jpeg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9c/Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet1.jpeg/759px-Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet1.jpeg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":308,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":508.4065934065934,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Money. This is not a profession which pays well quickly, you cannot expect to earn a living wage during apprenticeship and likely will need another job before pursuing this as your main source of income. Having this experience on your hands may help you obtain a music related job. Most of your money will be put into purchasing woods if you already have the tools and many people would rather pass up buying your guitar for something made inside established factories. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9e/Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet2.jpeg/460px-Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet2.jpeg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9e/Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet2.jpeg/759px-Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet2.jpeg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":308,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":508.4065934065934,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Connections to established Luthiers with whom to apprentice. Understand that what you know in the business is far less important than who you know. People will be a huge asset to you. Begin cultivating those friendships as soon and as diligently as possible, they will help in the long run to get popularity and get your builds sold. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1b/Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet3.jpeg/460px-Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet3.jpeg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1b/Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet3.jpeg/759px-Become-a-Luthier-2-bullet3.jpeg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":308,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":508.4065934065934,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
